{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UqZxTPA8qn6ZF9mkbqtTxh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.context;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n     4→\n     5→import java.security.Principal;\n     6→\n     7→public class EmptySecurityContext implements SecurityContext {\n     8→    @Override\n     9→    public Principal getUserPrincipal() {\n    10→        return null;\n    11→    }\n    12→\n    13→    @Override\n    14→    public boolean isUserInRole(String s) {\n    15→        return false;\n    16→    }\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public boolean isSecure() {\n    20→        return false;\n    21→    }\n    22→\n    23→    @Override\n    24→    public String getAuthenticationScheme() {\n    25→        return null;\n    26→    }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"0c83cab9-9e3e-4f09-b535-3f7b9884a454"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019x7uMnXuCkSMZLkTrCd841","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants;\n     2→\n     3→public class ValidationMessages {\n     4→\n     5→  public static final String SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK = \"slug must be not blank\";\n     6→  public static final String COMMENT_ID_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL = \"id must be not null\";\n     7→  public static final String REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL = \"request body must be not null\";\n     8→  public static final String USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK = \"username must be not blank\";\n     9→  public static final String EMAIL_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK = \"email must be not blank\";\n    10→  public static final String PASSWORD_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK = \"password must be not blank\";\n    11→  public static final String TITLE_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK = \"title must not be blank\";\n    12→  public static final String DESCRIPTION_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK = \"description must not be blank\";\n    13→  public static final String BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK = \"body must not be blank\";\n    14→}\n    15→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"2833ffb7-3262-4d86-bd75-fa2053c530cb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01L539Jb2KkvpaUffHUNgvn3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleModelBuilder;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationship;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class EntityUtils {\n    19→\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    @Named(\"usermodelbuilder\")\n    22→    private UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    private CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    29→\n    30→    public User user(UserEntity userEntity) {\n    31→        final var id = userEntity.getId();\n    32→        final var username = userEntity.getUsername();\n    33→        final var bio = userEntity.getBio();\n    34→        final var image = userEntity.getImage();\n    35→        final var password = userEntity.getPassword();\n    36→        final var email = userEntity.getEmail();\n    37→        return userBuilder.build(id, username, bio, image, password, email);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public Tag tag(TagEntity tagEntity) {\n    41→        return tagBuilder.build(tagEntity.getId(), tagEntity.getName());\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    public Tag tag(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    45→        return tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getTag());\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public TagRelationship tagRelationship(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    49→        return new TagRelationship(article(tagRelationshipEntity.getArticle()), tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getTag()));\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    public Article article(ArticleEntity articleEntity) {\n    53→        return articleBuilder.build(\n    54→                articleEntity.getId(),\n    55→                articleEntity.getSlug(),\n    56→                articleEntity.getTitle(),\n    57→                articleEntity.getDescription(),\n    58→                articleEntity.getBody(),\n    59→                articleEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    60→                articleEntity.getUpdatedAt(),\n    61→                user(articleEntity.getAuthor()));\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    public Comment comment(CommentEntity commentEntity) {\n    65→        return commentBuilder.build(\n    66→                commentEntity.getId(),\n    67→                user(commentEntity.getAuthor()),\n    68→                article(commentEntity.getArticle()),\n    69→                commentEntity.getBody(),\n    70→                commentEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    71→                commentEntity.getUpdatedAt());\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    public FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship(\n    75→            FavoriteRelationshipEntity favoriteRelationshipEntity) {\n    76→        return new FavoriteRelationship(\n    77→                user(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getUser()),\n    78→                article(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getArticle()));\n    79→    }\n    80→}\n    81→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"bfe7820a-ea1e-44e0-8e65-acfdb428a42d"}
