{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BPKpkJQMK95t5BDra2G4yR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.ArticleNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleById;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindArticleByIdImpl implements FindArticleById {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Article handle(UUID id) {\n    20→        return articleRepository.findArticleById(id).orElseThrow(ArticleNotFoundException::new);\n    21→    }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"38ee2141-32c2-4f3f-b394-c58d4c2273b6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SXoJ9AfFP8KWqG4maZrQYP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n     9→\n    10→@Dependent\n    11→public class FindUserByUsernameImpl implements FindUserByUsername {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    15→\n    16→    @Override\n    17→    public User handle(String username) {\n    18→        return userRepository.findByUsername(username).orElseThrow(UserNotFoundException::new);\n    19→    }\n    20→}\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"eefa91f5-01ae-465f-835d-c406acfe8b24"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019F36qL9pk4eknsCwT2qAni","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.ArticleNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindArticleByAuthorAndSlugImpl implements FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Article handle(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    20→        return articleRepository\n    21→                .findByAuthorAndSlug(authorId, slug)\n    22→                .orElseThrow(ArticleNotFoundException::new);\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"23537271-1d6a-4af0-a7e3-43e253f6fdab"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ShERbAy7NwsCaMiECkFuGb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FavoriteArticle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    11→\n    12→import java.util.UUID;\n    13→\n    14→@Singleton\n    15→public class FavoriteArticleImpl implements FavoriteArticle {\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    23→\n    24→    @Override\n    25→    public FavoriteRelationship handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    26→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    27→        final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    28→                favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    29→        return favoriteRelationshipOptional.orElseGet(() -> createFavoriteRelationship(currentUserId, article));\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    private FavoriteRelationship createFavoriteRelationship(UUID currentUserId, Article article) {\n    33→        final var user = findUserById.handle(currentUserId);\n    34→        final var favoriteRelationship = new FavoriteRelationship(user, article);\n    35→        favoriteRelationshipRepository.save(favoriteRelationship);\n    36→        return favoriteRelationship;\n    37→    }\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"643dddff-1400-47eb-900b-75bd9ace3d46"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01191nJJe575hvhPfKSCSNys","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfavoriteArticle;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class UnfavoriteArticleImpl implements UnfavoriteArticle {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public void handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    21→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    22→        final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    23→                favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    24→        favoriteRelationshipOptional.ifPresent(favoriteRelationshipRepository::delete);\n    25→    }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"95d34f37-2509-462b-88b1-e61a6a904f98"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GhmnX9mEQztNpa3GbdK7eo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FollowUserByUsername;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n    10→\n    11→import java.util.UUID;\n    12→\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class FollowUserByUsernameImpl implements FollowUserByUsername {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    private FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    private FollowRelationshipRepository usersFollowedRepository;\n    22→\n    23→    @Override\n    24→    public FollowRelationship handle(UUID loggedUserId, String username) {\n    25→        final var loggedUser = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    26→        final var userToFollow = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    27→        final var followingRelationship = new FollowRelationship(loggedUser, userToFollow);\n    28→        usersFollowedRepository.save(followingRelationship);\n    29→        return followingRelationship;\n    30→    }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"0e264f4a-78b9-419b-8693-74cc3bed8dc5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F2Kc9gGMr4ZMM8d7iS94Qz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfollowUserByUsername;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class UnfollowUserByUsernameImpl implements UnfollowUserByUsername {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FollowRelationshipRepository followRelationshipRepository;\n    21→\n    22→    @Override\n    23→    public void handle(UUID loggedUserId, String username) {\n    24→        final var loggedUser = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    25→        final var userToUnfollow = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    26→        final var followingRelationship =\n    27→                followRelationshipRepository.findByUsers(loggedUser, userToUnfollow).orElseThrow();\n    28→        followRelationshipRepository.remove(followingRelationship);\n    29→    }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"79ce7514-8dc0-4d5f-a783-1824d60b2e48"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RSy8GzMb4q8jAPjASEfeL7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.EmailAlreadyExistsException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UsernameAlreadyExistsException;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UpdateUser;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UpdateUserInput;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.UUID;\n    15→\n    16→@Dependent\n    17→public class UpdateUserImpl implements UpdateUser {\n    18→\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    25→\n    26→    @Override\n    27→    public User handle(UpdateUserInput updateUserInput) {\n    28→        final var user = findUserById.handle(updateUserInput.getId());\n    29→        checkValidations(updateUserInput, updateUserInput.getId());\n    30→        updateFields(user, updateUserInput);\n    31→        userRepository.update(modelValidator.validate(user));\n    32→        return user;\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→    private void updateFields(User user, UpdateUserInput updateUserInput) {\n    36→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getUsername())) {\n    37→            user.setUsername(updateUserInput.getUsername());\n    38→        }\n    39→\n    40→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getEmail())) {\n    41→            user.setEmail(updateUserInput.getEmail());\n    42→        }\n    43→\n    44→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getBio())) {\n    45→            user.setBio(updateUserInput.getBio());\n    46→        }\n    47→\n    48→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getImage())) {\n    49→            user.setImage(updateUserInput.getImage());\n    50→        }\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    private void checkValidations(UpdateUserInput updateUserInput, UUID excludeId) {\n    54→\n    55→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getUsername())) {\n    56→            checkUsername(excludeId, updateUserInput.getUsername());\n    57→        }\n    58→\n    59→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getEmail())) {\n    60→            checkEmail(excludeId, updateUserInput.getEmail());\n    61→        }\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    private boolean isPresent(String property) {\n    65→        return property != null && !property.isEmpty();\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    private void checkUsername(UUID selfId, String username) {\n    69→        if (userRepository.existsUsername(selfId, username)) {\n    70→            throw new UsernameAlreadyExistsException();\n    71→        }\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    private void checkEmail(UUID selfId, String email) {\n    75→        if (userRepository.existsEmail(selfId, email)) {\n    76→            throw new EmailAlreadyExistsException();\n    77→        }\n    78→    }\n    79→}\n    80→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"fd9d28b0-52f9-4645-a30e-dbd3863e0b79"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QKYj2fD6WqnLYyuhD4vMEo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateSlugByTitle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UpdateArticleBySlug;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.UpdateArticleInput;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n    12→\n    13→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n    14→\n    15→import static org.apache.commons.lang3.StringUtils.isNotBlank;\n    16→\n    17→@Singleton\n    18→public class UpdateArticleBySlugImpl implements UpdateArticleBySlug {\n    19→\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    22→    @Inject\n    23→    private CreateSlugByTitle createSlugByTitle;\n    24→    @Inject\n    25→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    26→    @Inject\n    27→    private ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    28→\n    29→    @Override\n    30→    public Article handle(UpdateArticleInput updateArticleInput) {\n    31→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(updateArticleInput.getSlug());\n    32→        if (atLeastOneFieldIsNotBlank(updateArticleInput)) {\n    33→            if (isNotBlank(updateArticleInput.getTitle())) {\n    34→                article.setSlug(createSlugByTitle.handle(updateArticleInput.getTitle()));\n    35→                article.setTitle(updateArticleInput.getTitle());\n    36→            }\n    37→            if (isNotBlank(updateArticleInput.getDescription())) {\n    38→                article.setDescription(updateArticleInput.getDescription());\n    39→            }\n    40→            if (isNotBlank(updateArticleInput.getBody())) {\n    41→                article.setBody(updateArticleInput.getBody());\n    42→            }\n    43→            article.setUpdatedAt(LocalDateTime.now());\n    44→            articleRepository.update(modelValidator.validate(article));\n    45→        }\n    46→        return article;\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    private boolean atLeastOneFieldIsNotBlank(UpdateArticleInput updateArticleInput) {\n    50→        return isNotBlank(updateArticleInput.getTitle())\n    51→                || isNotBlank(updateArticleInput.getDescription())\n    52→                || isNotBlank(updateArticleInput.getBody());\n    53→    }\n    54→}\n    55→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"29d2b6e8-c796-4d0a-bf11-9085e58507ce"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RzfyU7PBrAgvLRNWkpeSuV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.LoginUserInput;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    12→\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class LoginUserImpl implements LoginUser {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    private HashProvider hashProvider;\n    20→\n    21→    @Override\n    22→    public User handle(LoginUserInput loginUserInput) {\n    23→        final var user =\n    24→                userRepository\n    25→                        .findByEmail(loginUserInput.getEmail())\n    26→                        .orElseThrow(UserNotFoundException::new);\n    27→        if (!isPasswordValid(loginUserInput.getPassword(), user.getPassword())) {\n    28→            throw new InvalidPasswordException();\n    29→        }\n    30→        return user;\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    private boolean isPasswordValid(String password, String hashedPassword) {\n    34→        return hashProvider.checkPassword(password, hashedPassword);\n    35→    }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"625f2b96-39ca-435b-a5f6-a56c98ac6526"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHskdffdSFPRx2h7RnV2X7","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have read a comprehensive amount of the codebase. Let me provide a detailed summary of ALL the code I've read. Given the extensive nature of this project, let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n# COMPLETE JAKARTA TO SPRING MIGRATION - SOURCE CODE SUMMARY\n\n## PROJECT OVERVIEW\nThis is a RealWorld API implementation using Jakarta EE with OpenLiberty, JPA/Hibernate, MicroProfile, and JAX-RS. The application needs to be migrated from Jakarta EE to Spring Boot.\n\n## FILE STRUCTURE\n\n### Configuration Files\n\n**File: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/start.sh**\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\n# Start PostgreSQL\npg_ctlcluster $(pg_lsclusters -h | head -1 | awk '{print $1, $2}') start\n\n# Create database and user\nsu - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"CREATE USER postgres_user WITH PASSWORD 'S3cret';\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\nsu - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"CREATE DATABASE postgres_db OWNER postgres_user;\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\nsu - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE postgres_db TO postgres_user;\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\n\nexec mvn clean liberty:run\n```\n\n**File: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml**\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<persistence xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence\"\n             xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n             xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence/persistence_3_0.xsd\"\n             version=\"3.0\">\n    <persistence-unit name=\"realWorld-jpa\" transaction-type=\"JTA\">\n        <description>JPA Unit for RealWorld containing Users</description>\n        <jta-data-source>jdbc/RealWorldSource</jta-data-source>\n        <properties>\n            <property name=\"jakarta.persistence.schema-generation.database.action\" value=\"drop-and-create\"/>\n        </properties>\n    </persistence-unit>\n</persistence>\n```\n\n**File: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/beans.xml**\n```xml\n<beans xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n       xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n       xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/beans_4_0.xsd\"\n       bean-discovery-mode=\"all\"\n       version=\"4.0\">\n</beans>\n```\n\n**File: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/microprofile-config.properties**\n```\njwt.issuer=users-service\njwt.expiration.time.minutes=10\njwt.secret=secret123\n```\n\n**File: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/liberty/config/server.xml**\n```xml\n<server description=\"Realworld Liberty server\">\n    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_HOSTNAME\" defaultValue=\"localhost\"/>\n    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_PORT\" defaultValue=\"5432\"/>\n    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_DBNAME\" defaultValue=\"postgres_db\"/>\n    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_USER\" defaultValue=\"postgres_user\"/>\n    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_PW\" defaultValue=\"S3cret\"/>\n\n    <featureManager>\n        <feature>beanValidation-3.0</feature>\n        <feature>jsonb-3.0</feature>\n        <feature>persistence-3.1</feature>\n        <feature>restfulWS-3.1</feature>\n        <feature>jdbc-4.3</feature>\n        <feature>mpJwt-2.1</feature>\n        <feature>mpConfig-3.0</feature>\n        <feature>mpHealth-4.0</feature>\n    </featureManager>\n\n    <httpEndpoint httpPort=\"8080\" httpsPort=\"9443\"\n                  id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\"/>\n\n    <webApplication contextRoot=\"/\" location=\"realworld-liberty.war\"/>\n\n    <library id=\"postgresqlLib\">\n        <fileset dir=\"jdbc\" includes=\"postgresql*.jar\"/>\n    </library>\n\n    <dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/RealWorldSource\">\n        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"postgresqlLib\"/>\n        <properties.postgresql serverName=\"${POSTGRESQL_HOSTNAME}\" portNumber=\"${POSTGRESQL_PORT}\"\n                               databaseName=\"${POSTGRESQL_DBNAME}\" user=\"${POSTGRESQL_USER}\"\n                               password=\"${POSTGRESQL_PW}\"/>\n    </dataSource>\n\n    <cors domain=\"/api\"\n          allowedOrigins=\"*\"\n          allowedMethods=\"GET, POST, PUT\"\n          allowedHeaders=\"*\"\n          allowCredentials=\"true\"\n          maxAge=\"3600\"/>\n\n    <mpJwt id=\"jwtHandler\" issuer=\"users-service\" authorizationHeaderScheme=\"Token \"/>\n</server>\n```\n\n### Application Entry Point\n\n**File: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/App.java**\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web;\n\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n\n@ApplicationPath(\"api\")\npublic class App extends Application {\n}\n```\n\n### REST Resources (Controllers)\n\nThe application has 5 main resource classes that handle REST endpoints:\n\n1. **UsersResource** - Registration and login\n2. **UserResource** - Current user operations\n3. **ArticlesResource** - Article CRUD, comments, favorites\n4. **ProfilesResource** - User profiles and following\n5. **TagsResource** - Tags listing\n\nAll use:\n- `jakarta.ws.rs.*` annotations (@Path, @GET, @POST, @PUT, @DELETE, @Produces, @Consumes)\n- `jakarta.inject.Inject` for dependency injection\n- `jakarta.transaction.Transactional` for transaction management\n- `jakarta.validation.Valid` for validation\n- Custom `@Secured` annotation for security\n- Jackson's ObjectMapper for JSON serialization\n- JAX-RS SecurityContext for authentication\n\n### Domain Model\n\n**Key Domain Classes:**\n- **User** - username, email, password (hashed), bio, image\n- **Article** - slug, title, description, body, createdAt, updatedAt, author (User)\n- **Comment** - author (User), article (Article), body, createdAt, updatedAt  \n- **Tag** - name\n- **FavoriteRelationship** - user, article\n- **FollowRelationship** - user (follower), followed (User)\n- **TagRelationship** - article, tag\n\nAll domain models use:\n- `jakarta.validation.constraints.*` for validation\n- Lombok annotations (@Data, @AllArgsConstructor, @Getter, @Setter)\n- Protected constructors with AccessLevel.PROTECTED\n\n### Repository Pattern\n\nRepositories are interfaces defining data access operations. Implementations use:\n- `jakarta.persistence.EntityManager` with `@PersistenceContext`\n- `jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery` and `jakarta.persistence.Query`\n- Named queries with `@NamedQuery`\n- JPQL for queries\n\n### Feature/Service Layer\n\nThe application uses a feature-oriented service layer with:\n- Interface definitions in `domain.feature`\n- Implementations in `domain.feature.impl`\n- Dependency injection with `@Inject`\n- Singleton or Dependent scopes with `@Singleton` or `@Dependent`\n\n**Feature Examples:**\n- CreateUser, LoginUser, UpdateUser, FindUserById, FindUserByUsername\n- CreateArticle, UpdateArticleBySlug, DeleteArticleBySlug, FindArticleBySlug\n- CreateComment, DeleteComment, FindCommentsByArticleSlug\n- FollowUserByUsername, UnfollowUserByUsername\n- FavoriteArticle, UnfavoriteArticle\n- CreateTag, FindTags, FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists\n\n### JPA Entities\n\nEntity classes use:\n- `jakarta.persistence.*` annotations (@Entity, @Table, @Id, @Column, @ManyToOne, @OneToMany, @JoinColumn)\n- Hibernate annotations (@CreationTimestamp, @UpdateTimestamp)\n- Bidirectional relationships with FetchType.LAZY\n- Update methods to sync with domain models\n\n**Entity Classes:**\n- UserEntity\n- ArticleEntity\n- CommentEntity\n- TagEntity\n- TagRelationshipEntity\n- FavoriteRelationshipEntity\n- FollowRelationshipEntity\n\n### Security Implementation\n\n**Authentication Filter:** `AuthenticationFilter`\n- Implements `ContainerRequestFilter`\n- Extracts JWT token from \"Authorization: Token {jwt}\" header\n- Validates token using `TokenProvider`\n- Sets SecurityContext (DecodedJWTSecurityContext or EmptySecurityContext)\n- Priority: `Priorities.AUTHENTICATION`\n\n**Authorization Filter:** `AuthorizationFilter`\n- Implements `ContainerRequestFilter`\n- Checks user roles against `@Secured` annotation\n- Priority: `Priorities.AUTHORIZATION`\n\n**Token Provider:** `JwtTokenProvider`\n- Implements JWT creation and verification\n- Uses Auth0 JWT library with HMAC512\n- Extracts roles from JWT claims\n- Configured via MicroProfile Config properties\n\n**Security Contexts:**\n- `DecodedJWTSecurityContext` - for authenticated requests\n- `EmptySecurityContext` - for unauthenticated requests\n\n**Secured Annotation:**\n- Custom `@NameBinding` annotation\n- Supports role-based access (Role.USER, Role.ADMIN)\n- Optional security with `optional = true`\n\n### Exception Handling\n\n**Business Exceptions:**\n- Base class: `BusinessException` with code and messages\n- Specific exceptions: UserNotFoundException, ArticleNotFoundException, EmailAlreadyExistsException, UsernameAlreadyExistsException, InvalidPasswordException, TagNotFoundException, CommentNotFoundException, ModelValidationException\n\n**Exception Mappers:**\n- `BusinessExceptionMapper` - maps business exceptions to HTTP responses\n- `BeanValidationExceptionMapper` - maps constraint violations\n- Both implement `ExceptionMapper<T>` and use `@Provider`\n\n### Infrastructure\n\n**Password Hashing:** `BCryptHashProvider`\n- Uses BCrypt library (at.favre.lib.crypto.bcrypt)\n- 12 rounds of hashing\n\n**Slug Generation:** `SlugifySlugProvider`\n- Uses slugify library\n- Adds UUID suffix for uniqueness\n\n**JSON Serialization:** `SerializerConfig`\n- Produces two ObjectMapper beans\n- Default with root value wrapping\n- NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper without wrapping\n- Registers JavaTimeModule for LocalDateTime\n\n**Model Validation:** `ModelValidator`\n- Uses Jakarta Bean Validation\n- Throws ModelValidationException on failure\n\n### Request/Response Models\n\n**Request Wrappers:**\n- NewUserRequestWrapper, LoginRequestWrapper, UpdateUserRequestWrapper\n- NewArticleRequestWrapper, UpdateArticleRequestWrapper  \n- NewCommentRequestWrapper\n- All use nested structure (e.g., `{\"user\": {...}}`)\n\n**Response Models:**\n- UserResponse, ProfileResponse\n- ArticleResponse, ArticlesResponse\n- CommentResponse, CommentsResponse\n- TagsResponse, ErrorResponse\n- Use `@JsonRootName` for root wrapping\n- Jackson `@JsonFormat` for date formatting\n\n### Maven Dependencies (from pom.xml)\n\n**Jakarta/MicroProfile:**\n- microprofile 7.1 (provided)\n\n**Libraries:**\n- commons-lang3 3.18.0\n- java-jwt 4.5.0\n- hibernate-core 7.1.0.Final\n- hibernate-validator 9.0.1.Final\n- slugify 3.0.7\n- json 20250517\n- lombok 1.18.38\n- postgresql 42.7.7\n- jackson-databind 2.19.2\n- jackson-datatype-jsr310 2.19.2\n- bcrypt 0.10.2\n\n**Testing:**\n- junit-jupiter 5.13.4\n- rest-assured 5.5.5\n- testcontainers 1.21.3\n- microshed-testing 0.9.2\n\n### E2E Test File\n\n**File: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/e2e/api-test.js**\n\nK6 test script covering:\n- User registration, login, and update\n- Article CRUD operations\n- Article filtering (by author, favorited, tag)\n- Article feed\n- Favorite/unfavorite articles\n- Comments CRUD\n- Profile operations (get, follow, unfollow)\n- Tags listing\n\nTests expect:\n- Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api\n- JWT token in \"Authorization: Token {jwt}\" header\n- JSON request/response bodies with root wrapping\n\n## KEY MIGRATION POINTS\n\n### Jakarta EE to Spring Replacements Needed:\n\n1. **Dependency Injection**\n   - `jakarta.inject.@Inject` → `@Autowired` or constructor injection\n   - `@Singleton` → `@Service` or `@Component`\n   - `@ApplicationScoped` → `@Service`\n   - `@Dependent` → `@Scope(\"prototype\")` or default\n\n2. **REST Layer**\n   - `jakarta.ws.rs.*` → Spring Web MVC annotations\n   - `@Path` → `@RequestMapping` or `@GetMapping`, etc.\n   - `@PathParam` → `@PathVariable`\n   - `@QueryParam` → `@RequestParam`\n   - `@Consumes/@Produces` → `@RequestMapping(consumes/produces)`\n   - JAX-RS Response → ResponseEntity<T>\n   - SecurityContext → Spring Security Authentication\n\n3. **JPA/Persistence**\n   - `@PersistenceContext EntityManager` → `@PersistenceContext` (same) or use Spring Data JPA repositories\n   - `jakarta.transaction.@Transactional` → `org.springframework.transaction.annotation.@Transactional`\n   - persistence.xml → application.properties/yaml\n\n4. **Validation**\n   - `jakarta.validation.*` → Compatible, but might use Spring Validation\n   - Bean validation still works\n\n5. **Configuration**\n   - MicroProfile Config → Spring Boot properties\n   - `@ConfigProperty` → `@Value` or `@ConfigurationProperties`\n\n6. **Security**\n   - Custom JWT filter → Spring Security filter chain\n   - `@Secured` annotation → `@PreAuthorize` or `@Secured` (Spring Security)\n   - SecurityContext → Spring Security context\n\n7. **Exception Handling**\n   - JAX-RS ExceptionMapper → `@ControllerAdvice` with `@ExceptionHandler`\n\n8. **JSON Serialization**\n   - CDI-produced ObjectMapper → Auto-configured by Spring Boot\n   - Jackson configuration in application.properties\n\n9. **Server Configuration**\n   - server.xml → application.properties/yaml\n   - DataSource configuration → Spring Boot auto-configuration\n\n10. **Build**\n    - Liberty Maven plugin → Spring Boot Maven plugin\n    - WAR packaging → JAR packaging (executable)\n\nThis completes the comprehensive source code summary for the Jakarta to Spring migration planning."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"2565c17a-2d96-444a-b1ec-9b967a14e316"}
