{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Gh5HaXsTjGoVkpKD22GxMK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import at.favre.lib.crypto.bcrypt.BCrypt;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     6→\n     7→@ApplicationScoped\n     8→public class BCryptHashProvider implements HashProvider {\n     9→\n    10→    @Override\n    11→    public String hashPassword(String password) {\n    12→        return BCrypt.withDefaults().hashToString(12, password.toCharArray());\n    13→    }\n    14→\n    15→    @Override\n    16→    public boolean checkPassword(String plaintext, String hashed) {\n    17→        return BCrypt.verifyer().verify(plaintext.toCharArray(), hashed).verified;\n    18→    }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DFZprR2V5kPdZPpQgHmuVR","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"4c37dce2-b211-4a21-93e0-b8f4ebb14e32"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Qhpv5KvzAV7hLL4fHMuTSc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.github.slugify.Slugify;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     7→\n     8→\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class SlugifySlugProvider implements SlugProvider {\n    11→\n    12→    private Slugify slugify;\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    public SlugifySlugProvider() {\n    16→        this.slugify = Slugify.builder().build();\n    17→    }\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public String slugify(String text) {\n    21→        return slugify.slugify(text);\n    22→    }\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DFZprR2V5kPdZPpQgHmuVR","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"3bcb6274-4867-4d9c-b804-001a41f6f297"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GLFyNT5N2dar6Sm8AuysFj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.Query;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity.*;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    12→\n    13→public abstract class AbstractDAO<ENTITY, ID> {\n    14→\n    15→    @PersistenceContext\n    16→    protected EntityManager em;\n    17→\n    18→    protected UserEntity findUserEntityById(UUID id) {\n    19→        return em.find(UserEntity.class, id);\n    20→    }\n    21→\n    22→    protected TagEntity findTagEntityById(UUID id) {\n    23→        return em.find(TagEntity.class, id);\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    protected ArticleEntity findArticleEntityById(UUID id) {\n    27→        return em.find(ArticleEntity.class, id);\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    protected CommentEntity findCommentEntityById(UUID id) {\n    31→        return em.find(CommentEntity.class, id);\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    protected FavoriteRelationshipEntity findFavoriteRelationshipEntityByKey(\n    35→            FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) {\n    36→\n    37→        Query query = em.createNamedQuery(\"FVREfindByArticleAndUserID\");\n    38→        query.setParameter(\"articleId\", favoriteRelationship.getArticle().getId());\n    39→        query.setParameter(\"currentUserId\", favoriteRelationship.getUser().getId());\n    40→\n    41→        List<FavoriteRelationshipEntity> resultList = query.getResultList();\n    42→        if (!resultList.isEmpty()) {\n    43→            return (resultList.get(0));\n    44→        } else {\n    45→            return null;\n    46→        }\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    protected boolean isNotEmpty(List<?> list) {\n    50→        return list != null && !list.isEmpty();\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    protected List<String> toUpperCase(List<String> subjectList) {\n    54→        return subjectList.stream().map(String::toUpperCase).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    55→    }\n    56→}\n    57→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DFZprR2V5kPdZPpQgHmuVR","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"6583d19e-6746-41e8-8fad-9e1ea050e018"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CrH3jaRsTEghVwpidx6HRd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.*;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    11→\n    12→import java.security.Principal;\n    13→import java.util.List;\n    14→import java.util.UUID;\n    15→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class ResourceUtils {\n    19→\n    20→    private static final int DEFAULT_LIMIT = 20;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private FindArticleTags findArticleTags;\n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    private IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited;\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    private ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount;\n    31→\n    32→    public ProfileResponse profileResponse(String username, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    33→        final var user = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    34→        final var profileResponse = new ProfileResponse(user);\n    35→        if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    36→            profileResponse.setFollowing(isFollowingUser.handle(loggedUserId, user.getId()));\n    37→        }\n    38→        return profileResponse;\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    public ArticleResponse articleResponse(Article article, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    42→        final var author = article.getAuthor();\n    43→        final var profileResponse = profileResponse(author.getUsername(), author.getId());\n    44→        final var tags = findArticleTags.handle(article);\n    45→        final var favoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount.handle(article.getId());\n    46→        final var articleResponse = new ArticleResponse(article, profileResponse, favoritesCount, tags);\n    47→        if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    48→            articleResponse.setFavorited(isArticleFavorited.handle(article, loggedUserId));\n    49→        }\n    50→        return articleResponse;\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    public ArticlesResponse articlesResponse(PageResult<Article> pageResult, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    54→        final var resultResponse = pageResult.getResult().stream().map(article -> articleResponse(article, loggedUserId)).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    55→        return new ArticlesResponse(resultResponse, pageResult.getTotal());\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public CommentResponse commentResponse(Comment comment, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    59→        final var commentAuthor = comment.getAuthor();\n    60→        final var authorResponse = profileResponse(commentAuthor.getUsername(), loggedUserId);\n    61→        return new CommentResponse(comment, authorResponse);\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    public UUID getLoggedUserId(SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    65→        Principal principal = securityContext.getUserPrincipal();\n    66→        return principal != null ? UUID.fromString(principal.getName()) : null;\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    public CommentsResponse commentsResponse(List<Comment> comments, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    70→        final var resultResponse = comments.stream().map(comment -> commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId)).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    71→        return new CommentsResponse(resultResponse);\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    public int getLimit(int limit) {\n    75→        return limit > 0 ? limit : DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n    76→    }\n    77→}\n    78→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DFZprR2V5kPdZPpQgHmuVR","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"5dfacaf5-d337-4f18-b61a-76ff59d4b07e"}
