{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013Jz6Zw9KbKvVbGhEsQDywD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.DeleteComment;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\n     9→\n    10→@Singleton\n    11→public class DeleteCommentImpl implements DeleteComment {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private FindCommentByIdAndAuthor findCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public void handle(DeleteCommentInput deleteCommentInput) {\n    20→        final var comment =\n    21→                findCommentByIdAndAuthor.handle(\n    22→                        deleteCommentInput.getCommentId(), deleteCommentInput.getAuthorId());\n    23→        commentRepository.delete(comment);\n    24→    }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DHi4ffhC8WvQoxVRZ6J6CP","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"98e42061-2ebe-4a5a-9772-80c9cf455503"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WjuK6QWquAWQHEZYwCXfRL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FavoriteArticle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    11→\n    12→import java.util.UUID;\n    13→\n    14→@Singleton\n    15→public class FavoriteArticleImpl implements FavoriteArticle {\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    23→\n    24→    @Override\n    25→    public FavoriteRelationship handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    26→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    27→        final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    28→                favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    29→        return favoriteRelationshipOptional.orElseGet(() -> createFavoriteRelationship(currentUserId, article));\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    private FavoriteRelationship createFavoriteRelationship(UUID currentUserId, Article article) {\n    33→        final var user = findUserById.handle(currentUserId);\n    34→        final var favoriteRelationship = new FavoriteRelationship(user, article);\n    35→        favoriteRelationshipRepository.save(favoriteRelationship);\n    36→        return favoriteRelationship;\n    37→    }\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DHi4ffhC8WvQoxVRZ6J6CP","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"569835c4-748c-490d-9d08-ef8769f95c00"}
