{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017ygK4EXceJ4xmrMGDMGhgP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.ArticleNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindArticleByAuthorAndSlugImpl implements FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Article handle(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    20→        return articleRepository\n    21→                .findByAuthorAndSlug(authorId, slug)\n    22→                .orElseThrow(ArticleNotFoundException::new);\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DHi4ffhC8WvQoxVRZ6J6CP","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"eaa157e6-3f22-4247-a255-01a4f7dbfd2c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JKSCv59GcEs1viTMhYuiFh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.LoginUserInput;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    12→\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class LoginUserImpl implements LoginUser {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    private HashProvider hashProvider;\n    20→\n    21→    @Override\n    22→    public User handle(LoginUserInput loginUserInput) {\n    23→        final var user =\n    24→                userRepository\n    25→                        .findByEmail(loginUserInput.getEmail())\n    26→                        .orElseThrow(UserNotFoundException::new);\n    27→        if (!isPasswordValid(loginUserInput.getPassword(), user.getPassword())) {\n    28→            throw new InvalidPasswordException();\n    29→        }\n    30→        return user;\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    private boolean isPasswordValid(String password, String hashedPassword) {\n    34→        return hashProvider.checkPassword(password, hashedPassword);\n    35→    }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DHi4ffhC8WvQoxVRZ6J6CP","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"a26de44c-d2c5-4668-be0e-240c777cd38b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01P4o6BFjdayV9JjMVX2MQH3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfavoriteArticle;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class UnfavoriteArticleImpl implements UnfavoriteArticle {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public void handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    21→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    22→        final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    23→                favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    24→        favoriteRelationshipOptional.ifPresent(favoriteRelationshipRepository::delete);\n    25→    }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DHi4ffhC8WvQoxVRZ6J6CP","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"59132d0c-c9a5-4a73-82ed-ebae39249760"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015DUbXKgSFWH9TvpCczE9DG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfollowUserByUsername;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class UnfollowUserByUsernameImpl implements UnfollowUserByUsername {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FollowRelationshipRepository followRelationshipRepository;\n    21→\n    22→    @Override\n    23→    public void handle(UUID loggedUserId, String username) {\n    24→        final var loggedUser = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    25→        final var userToUnfollow = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    26→        final var followingRelationship =\n    27→                followRelationshipRepository.findByUsers(loggedUser, userToUnfollow).orElseThrow();\n    28→        followRelationshipRepository.remove(followingRelationship);\n    29→    }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DHi4ffhC8WvQoxVRZ6J6CP","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"1faf7e60-