{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011zeEbWTJ2BLKLmJ6GYUhc8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01JwWofMLrBkFHqCR26xoHD1","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Create Spring config files","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE (OpenLiberty) application to Spring Boot. Create the following files:\n\n**1. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/application.properties**\n\nThe original app used:\n- PostgreSQL with: host=localhost, port=5432, db=postgres_db, user=postgres_user, password=S3cret\n- JPA with Hibernate, schema generation: drop-and-create\n- JWT config: issuer=users-service, secret=secret123, expiration=10 minutes\n\nCreate application.properties with:\n```\nserver.port=8080\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/postgres_db\nspring.datasource.username=postgres_user\nspring.datasource.password=S3cret\nspring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.postgresql.Driver\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.properties.hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\njwt.issuer=users-service\njwt.secret=secret123\njwt.expiration.time.minutes=10\n```\n\n**2. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/App.java**\n\nReplace the existing JAX-RS Application class with a Spring Boot main application:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.domain.EntityScan;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaRepositories;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@ComponentScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi\")\n@EntityScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity\")\npublic class App {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(App.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**3. Delete/remove these Jakarta-specific files (they won't be needed):**\n- src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml\n- src/main/resources/META-INF/beans.xml\n- src/main/resources/META-INF/microprofile-config.properties\n- src/main/liberty/config/server.xml (entire liberty directory)\n\nWrite all three files. For the deletions, just note them - the main task will handle deleting.\n\nDo this now using the Write tool for creating files.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2657,"cache_read_input_tokens":109948,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2657,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":855},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"cf7f24e8-09ef-41d5-8c7a-f386154b8f47"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE (OpenLiberty) application to Spring Boot. Create the following files:\n\n**1. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/application.properties**\n\nThe original app used:\n- PostgreSQL with: host=localhost, port=5432, db=postgres_db, user=postgres_user, password=S3cret\n- JPA with Hibernate, schema generation: drop-and-create\n- JWT config: issuer=users-service, secret=secret123, expiration=10 minutes\n\nCreate application.properties with:\n```\nserver.port=8080\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/postgres_db\nspring.datasource.username=postgres_user\nspring.datasource.password=S3cret\nspring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.postgresql.Driver\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.properties.hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\njwt.issuer=users-service\njwt.secret=secret123\njwt.expiration.time.minutes=10\n```\n\n**2. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/App.java**\n\nReplace the existing JAX-RS Application class with a Spring Boot main application:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.domain.EntityScan;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaRepositories;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@ComponentScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi\")\n@EntityScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity\")\npublic class App {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(App.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**3. Delete/remove these Jakarta-specific files (they won't be needed):**\n- src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml\n- src/main/resources/META-INF/beans.xml\n- src/main/resources/META-INF/microprofile-config.properties\n- src/main/liberty/config/server.xml (entire liberty directory)\n\nWrite all three files. For the deletions, just note them - the main task will handle deleting.\n\nDo this now using the Write tool for creating files."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JwWofMLrBkFHqCR26xoHD1","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"11fab927-fc6f-47b8-be13-bc8bf89b9d7f"}
