example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/filter/AuthenticationFilter.java\n-rw-r-----. 1 bmcginn users 3.4K Mar 14 03:23 /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/filter/AuthorizationFilter.java\n-rw-r-----. 1 bmcginn users 2.6K Mar 14 06:03 /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/filter/JwtAuthenticationFilter.java\n\nConfiguration:\n-rw-r-----. 1 bmcginn users 1.1K Mar 14 06:04 /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/config/SerializerConfig.java\n\nException Handler:\n-rw-r-----. 1 bmcginn users 5.1K Mar 14 06:03 /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/GlobalExceptionHandler.java\n\nUtility Component:\n-rw-r-----. 1 bmcginn users 4.0K Mar 14 06:04 /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Fkf2BLTJJ9RRFru2UCSEoP","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"9f35a575-01e0-4c53-abb0-438ac81fe5ce"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Fkf2BLTJJ9RRFru2UCSEoP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All files have been successfully created. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Migration Complete: Jakarta EE to Spring Boot\n\nI have successfully written all 10 files for your Spring Boot migration:\n\n### **Controllers (JAX-RS → Spring MVC)**\n\n1. **ArticlesResource.java** (9.7 KB)\n   - Converted from `@Path` to `@RestController` + `@RequestMapping(\"/api/articles\")`\n   - Changed JAX-RS annotations to Spring MVC equivalents\n   - Replaced Jakarta CDI `@Inject` with constructor injection\n   - Uses `@Qualifier` for ObjectMapper beans\n   - SecurityContext replaced with `resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId()`\n\n2. **UsersResource.java** (3.1 KB)\n   - Handles user registration and login\n   - Returns `ResponseEntity<String>` instead of JAX-RS `Response`\n   - Proper HTTP status codes with Spring's `HttpStatus`\n\n3. **UserResource.java** (2.8 KB)\n   - GET and PUT endpoints for current user\n   - Uses Spring Security integration via ResourceUtils\n\n4. **ProfilesResource.java** (2.8 KB)\n   - Profile viewing and follow/unfollow functionality\n   - Full Spring MVC conversion\n\n5. **TagsResource.java** (970 bytes)\n   - Simple tags endpoint\n   - Clean Spring MVC implementation\n\n### **Infrastructure Components**\n\n6. **ResourceUtils.java** (4.0 KB)\n   - Changed from `@ApplicationScoped` to Spring `@Component`\n   - Replaced SecurityContext parameter with `SecurityContextHolder.getContext().getAuthentication()`\n   - Constructor-based dependency injection\n\n7. **SecurityConfig.java** (2.6 KB)\n   - Spring Security configuration with `SecurityFilterChain`\n   - CORS configuration\n   - Public/authenticated endpoint rules\n   - Stateless session management\n\n8. **JwtAuthenticationFilter.java** (2.6 KB)\n   - Extends Spring's `OncePerRequestFilter`\n   - Replaces both JAX-RS AuthenticationFilter and AuthorizationFilter\n   - Extracts JWT tokens and sets Spring Security context\n\n9. **SerializerConfig.java** (1.1 KB)\n   - Converted from Jakarta CDI to Spring `@Configuration`\n   - Two ObjectMapper beans with `@Qualifier` names\n   - `@Primary` annotation for default mapper\n\n10. **GlobalExceptionHandler.java** (5.1 KB)\n    - Replaced JAX-RS `ExceptionMapper` classes with Spring `@RestControllerAdvice`\n    - Handles all domain and infrastructure exceptions\n    - Returns proper HTTP status codes and JSON error responses\n\n### **Key Migration Changes Applied**\n\n- **Dependency Injection**: Jakarta CDI (`@Inject`, `@ApplicationScoped`) → Spring (`@Component`, constructor injection, `@Autowired`)\n- **REST Annotations**: JAX-RS (`@Path`, `@GET`, `@POST`) → Spring MVC (`@RestController`, `@GetMapping`, `@PostMapping`)\n- **Path/Query Parameters**: `@PathParam`, `@QueryParam` → `@PathVariable`, `@RequestParam`\n- **Security**: JAX-RS `SecurityContext` → Spring Security `SecurityContextHolder`\n- **Transactions**: `jakarta.transaction.Transactional` → `org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional`\n- **Configuration**: Jakarta CDI producers → Spring `@Bean` methods\n- **Exception Handling**: JAX-RS `ExceptionMapper` → Spring `@RestControllerAdvice`\n\nAll files have been successfully created in their respective directories with proper Spring Boot conventions!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"ed38713d-0a1f-4ebe-a3b0-a96cd9803c9e"}
