{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012Nwi8fcGmuucBaamjaWJmR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.ArticleFavoritesCount;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleById;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class ArticleFavoritesCountImpl implements ArticleFavoritesCount {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FindArticleById findArticleById;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public long handle(UUID articleId) {\n    21→        final var article = findArticleById.handle(articleId);\n    22→        return favoriteRelationshipRepository.favoritesCount(article);\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015GtPhiKuyszHuNBzavn66f","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"3033a24c-adc8-4685-b619-24982f6d4e63"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UsCfXz86TsD1LhYEeUSVrM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateComment;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.NewCommentInput;\n    12→\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class CreateCommentImpl implements CreateComment {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    22→    @Inject\n    23→    private CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    24→\n    25→    @Override\n    26→    public Comment handle(NewCommentInput newCommentInput) {\n    27→        final var author = findUserById.handle(newCommentInput.getAuthorId());\n    28→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(newCommentInput.getArticleSlug());\n    29→        final var comment = commentBuilder.build(author, article, newCommentInput.getBody());\n    30→        commentRepository.save(comment);\n    31→        return comment;\n    32→    }\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015GtPhiKuyszHuNBzavn66f","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"23a9ba54-add7-4e4c-a73c-d40f6583b76e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VqCBraTv3U5WUQMDyKNip5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateSlugByTitle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class CreateSlugByTitleImpl implements CreateSlugByTitle {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private SlugProvider slugProvider;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public String handle(String title) {\n    21→        String slug = slugProvider.slugify(title);\n    22→        if (articleRepository.existsBySlug(slug)) {\n    23→            slug += UUID.randomUUID().toString();\n    24→        }\n    25→        return slug;\n    26→    }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015GtPhiKuyszHuNBzavn66f","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"9ac6b647-877b-43e9-ac0d-51625f03c043"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XZTYXwRgjpuMdDDW4SwayL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateTag;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     9→\n    10→@Singleton\n    11→public class CreateTagImpl implements CreateTag {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private TagRepository tagRepository;\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Tag handle(String name) {\n    20→        final var tag = tagBuilder.build(name);\n    21→        tagRepository.save(tag);\n    22→        return tag;\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015GtPhiKuyszHuNBzavn66f","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"26e7a339-b595-4f25-977e-50999ea98956"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FvJguLRVGxEg4L9eMr8QRU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.DeleteArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationshipRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.List;\n    15→import java.util.Optional;\n    16→import java.util.UUID;\n    17→\n    18→@Singleton\n    19→public class DeleteArticleBySlugImpl implements DeleteArticleBySlug {\n    20→\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug findArticleByAuthorAndSlug;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private TagRelationshipRepository tagRelationshipRepository;\n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    31→\n    32→    @Override\n    33→    public void handle(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    34→        final var article = findArticleByAuthorAndSlug.handle(authorId, slug);\n    35→        tagRelationshipRepository.delete(article);\n    36→        Optional<FavoriteRelationship> favorite = favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), authorId);\n    37→        favorite.ifPresent(favoriteRelationship -> favoriteRelationshipRepository.delete(favoriteRelationship));\n    38→        List<Comment> comments = commentRepository.findCommentsByArticle(article);\n    39→        comments.forEach(c -> commentRepository.delete(c));\n    40→        articleRepository.delete(article);\n    41→    }\n    42→}\n    43→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015GtPhiKuyszHuNBzavn66f","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"db9bfbe2-6bdd-4207-9d12-f96a3fc686a8"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_017bNemi72g5fEh8CsmBA8Wx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01LcURB7xnfoyHPMVv5o1bFo","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/feature/impl/ArticleFavoritesCountImpl.java","content":"package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.ArticleFavoritesCount;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleById;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\n@Service\npublic class ArticleFavoritesCountImpl implements ArticleFavoritesCount {\n\n    private final FindArticleById findArticleById;\n    private final FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n\n    public ArticleFavoritesCountImpl(FindArticleById findArticleById,\n                                     FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository) {\n        this.findArticleById = findArticleById;\n        this.favoriteRelationshipRepository = favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public long handle(UUID articleId) {\n        final var article = findArticleById.handle(articleId);\n        return favoriteRelationshipRepository.favoritesCount(article);\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3255,"cache_read_input_tokens":96698,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3255,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2513},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015GtPhiKuyszHuNBzavn66f","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"6b9c5e55-e5e2-495c-8aae-6e1d3