{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The conversation is summarized below:\nAnalysis:\nLet me chronologically analyze the conversation:\n\n1. **User's Initial Request**: The user requested a complete migration of a Java application from Jakarta EE (OpenLiberty) to Spring Boot. This is a comprehensive one-shot migration with specific requirements around Docker isolation, testing, and documentation.\n\n2. **Phase 1 - Codebase Analysis**: I explored the entire project structure, which is a RealWorld API (Conduit) application built with:\n   - Jakarta EE with MicroProfile on OpenLiberty\n   - JAX-RS for REST endpoints\n   - CDI for dependency injection\n   - JPA with Hibernate for persistence\n   - PostgreSQL database\n   - Custom JWT authentication\n   - Maven build system\n   - Docker containerization\n\n3. **Phase 2 - Reading all source files**: I systematically read every Java source file in the project to understand the full architecture. The app has ~80+ Java files organized in:\n   - application/web/resource (REST controllers)\n   - application/web/model (request/response DTOs)\n   - domain/feature (business logic interfaces + implementations)\n   - domain/model (domain entities, repositories, builders)\n   - domain/exception (business exceptions)\n   - domain/validator (model validation)\n   - infrastructure/provider (JWT, BCrypt, Slugify)\n   - infrastructure/repository (DAOs with JPA EntityManager)\n   - infrastructure/repository/entity (JPA entities)\n   - infrastructure/web (security filters, exception mappers, config)\n\n4. **Phase 3 - Smoke test creation**: Created smoke.py with comprehensive API tests covering all endpoints.\n\n5. **Phase 4 - pom.xml rewrite**: Replaced Jakarta EE dependencies (MicroProfile, Liberty, etc.) with Spring Boot starters (web, data-jpa, validation, security).\n\n6. **Phase 5 - Application configuration**: Created application.properties and rewrote App.java as Spring Boot main class. Removed Jakarta-specific config files (persistence.xml, beans.xml, microprofile-config.properties, server.xml).\n\n7. **Phase 6 - Controller migration**: Converted all 5 REST resource classes from JAX-RS to Spring MVC (@RestController, @GetMapping, etc.).\n\n8. **Phase 7 - Security migration**: Created SecurityConfig with Spring Security filter chain, and JwtAuthenticationFilter extending OncePerRequestFilter.\n\n9. **Phase 8 - Exception handling migration**: Created GlobalExceptionHandler with @RestControllerAdvice replacing JAX-RS ExceptionMapper classes.\n\n10. **Phase 9 - Service/Repository migration**: Converted all CDI beans to Spring components (@Service, @Repository, @Component). Changed field injection to constructor injection throughout.\n\n11. **Phase 10 - Cleanup**: Removed obsolete Jakarta-specific files (old filters, exception mappers, security contexts, qualifiers). Removed Jakarta JSON-B imports. Removed old Liberty-specific test files.\n\n12. **Phase 11 - Dockerfile/start.sh update**: Updated start.sh to use `mvn` instead of `./mvnw` (because .dockerignore excludes mvnw) and changed from `liberty:run` to `java -jar target/realworld-spring.jar`.\n\n13. **Phase 12 - Docker build and run**: Successfully built the Docker image and started the container. The Spring Boot application started successfully on port 8080 (mapped to host port 33734).\n\n**Errors encountered:**\n1. `.dockerignore` excluded mvnw and .mvn - Fixed by using `mvn` directly since the base image already has Maven.\n2. Dynamic port assignment syntax issue with bash - Worked around by getting port separately.\n\n**Current state**: The Spring Boot application is running successfully in Docker. The container shows:\n- Spring Boot v3.4.3 started\n- Hibernate connected to PostgreSQL\n- Tomcat started on port 8080\n- Application started in ~7 seconds\n\n**Pending**: \n- Execute smoke tests against the running container\n- Fix any issues found by smoke tests\n- Document everything in CHANGELOG.md\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user requested an autonomous, one-shot migration of a Java RealWorld API (Conduit) application from Jakarta EE (OpenLiberty with MicroProfile) to Spring Boot. The migration must follow a specific checklist: analyze codebase, generate smoke tests, update dependencies, refactor code, modify build configs/Dockerfile, build/run Docker container, execute smoke tests, and document everything in CHANGELOG.md. Docker isolation is required using `$SCARF_CONTAINER_NAME` and `$SCARF_IMAGE_TAG` environment variables with dynamic port allocation (`-p 0:8080`). The environment variables resolved to: `SCARF_CONTAINER_NAME=scarf_1773466949_876546_app`, `SCARF_IMAGE_TAG=scarf_1773466949_876546:latest`.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Jakarta EE → Spring Boot migration (JAX-RS → Spring MVC, CDI → Spring DI, MicroProfile → Spring Boot properties)\n   - JAX-RS annotations (@Path, @GET, @POST, @PathParam, @QueryParam) → Spring MVC (@RestController, @GetMapping, @PostMapping, @PathVariable, @RequestParam)\n   - CDI (@Inject, @Singleton, @ApplicationScoped, @Dependent) → Spring (@Service, @Repository, @Component, constructor injection)\n   - Jakarta Persistence (EntityManager, @PersistenceContext) retained as-is (Spring Boot supports Jakarta Persistence)\n   - Jakarta Validation (@Valid, @NotBlank, etc.) retained as-is\n   - Custom JWT authentication with \"Token \" prefix (not \"Bearer \")\n   - JAX-RS ContainerRequestFilter → Spring OncePerRequestFilter\n   - JAX-RS ExceptionMapper → Spring @RestControllerAdvice with @ExceptionHandler\n   - CDI @Produces → Spring @Bean in @Configuration\n   - MicroProfile @ConfigProperty → Spring @Value\n   - WAR packaging on OpenLiberty → JAR packaging with embedded Tomcat\n   - Two ObjectMapper beans: one with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE (primary), one without (qualified as \"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n   - Docker dynamic port allocation with `-p 0:8080`\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **pom.xml** (Modified)\n     - Replaced Jakarta EE/MicroProfile dependencies with Spring Boot starters\n     - Changed packaging from WAR to JAR\n     - Replaced liberty-maven-plugin with spring-boot-maven-plugin\n     - Key dependencies: spring-boot-starter-web, spring-boot-starter-data-jpa, spring-boot-starter-validation, spring-boot-starter-security, postgresql, java-jwt 4.5.0, bcrypt 0.10.2, slugify 3.0.7, lombok\n     ```xml\n     <parent>\n         <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n         <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>\n         <version>3.4.3</version>\n     </parent>\n     <packaging>jar</packaging>\n     <artifactId>realworld-spring</artifactId>\n     ```\n\n   - **src/main/resources/application.properties** (Created)\n     - Spring Boot configuration replacing persistence.xml, server.xml, and microprofile-config.properties\n     ```properties\n     server.port=8080\n     spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/postgres_db\n     spring.datasource.username=postgres_user\n     spring.datasource.password=S3cret\n     spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n     spring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n     jwt.issuer=users-service\n     jwt.secret=secret123\n     jwt.expiration.time.minutes=10\n     ```\n\n   - **src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/App.java** (Modified)\n     - Replaced JAX-RS Application class with Spring Boot main class\n     ```java\n     @SpringBootApplication\n     @ComponentScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi\")\n     @EntityScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity\")\n     public class App {\n         public static void main(String[] args) {\n             SpringApplication.run(App.class, args);\n         }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **ArticlesResource.java** (Modified) - Main REST controller with 13 endpoints for articles, comments, favorites. Uses constructor injection with @Qualifier for two ObjectMapper beans. Returns ResponseEntity<String>.\n\n   - **UsersResource.java** (Modified) - Registration and login endpoints at /api/users. Throws UnauthorizedException on login failure.\n\n   - **UserResource.java** (Modified) - Current user GET/PUT at /api/user. Uses ResourceUtils.getLoggedUserId().\n\n   - **ProfilesResource.java** (Modified) - Profile viewing and follow/unfollow at /api/profiles.\n\n   - **TagsResource.java** (Modified) - Simple GET /api/tags endpoint returning TagsResponse directly.\n\n   - **ResourceUtils.java** (Modified)\n     - Changed from @ApplicationScoped to @Component\n     - Key change: `getLoggedUserId()` now uses SecurityContextHolder instead of JAX-RS SecurityContext parameter\n     ```java\n     public UUID getLoggedUserId() {\n         var auth = SecurityContextHolder.getContext().getAuthentication();\n         if (auth != null && auth.getPrincipal() != null && !\"anonymousUser\".equals(auth.getPrincipal())) {\n             try { return UUID.fromString(auth.getName()); }\n             catch (IllegalArgumentException e) { return null; }\n         }\n         return null;\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **SecurityConfig.java** (Created)\n     - Spring Security configuration with stateless sessions\n     - Public endpoints: POST /api/users, POST /api/users/login, GET /api/articles/*, GET /api/tags, GET /api/profiles/*\n     - All other requests require authentication\n     ```java\n     @Configuration\n     @EnableWebSecurity\n     public class SecurityConfig { ... }\n     ```\n\n   - **JwtAuthenticationFilter.java** (Created)\n     - Replaces both old AuthenticationFilter and AuthorizationFilter\n     - Extends OncePerRequestFilter\n     - Extracts JWT from \"Token \" prefix header, sets Spring SecurityContext with UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken\n     ```java\n     @Component\n     public class JwtAuthenticationFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter { ... }\n     ```\n\n   - **SerializerConfig.java** (Modified)\n     - Changed from CDI @Produces to Spring @Bean\n     - Two named beans: \"wrappingObjectMapper\" (@Primary) and \"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\"\n\n   - **GlobalExceptionHandler.java** (Created)\n     - Replaces 3 JAX-RS ExceptionMapper classes (BusinessExceptionMapper, BeanValidationExceptionMapper, InfrastructureExceptionMapper)\n     - Handles: UserNotFoundException (404), ArticleNotFoundException (404), EmailAlreadyExistsException (409), UsernameAlreadyExistsException (409), InvalidPasswordException (401), ModelValidationException (422), UnauthorizedException (401), ForbiddenException (403), ConstraintViolationException (422)\n\n   - **JwtTokenProvider.java** (Modified)\n     - @ApplicationScoped → @Service\n     - @ConfigProperty → @Value(\"${jwt.issuer}\"), @Value(\"${jwt.secret}\"), @Value(\"${jwt.expiration.time.minutes}\")\n\n   - **BCryptHashProvider.java, SlugifySlugProvider.java** (Modified) - @ApplicationScoped → @Service\n\n   - **ModelValidator.java** (Modified) - @Singleton → @Component, constructor injection for jakarta.validation.Validator\n\n   - **All DAO files** (Modified) - @Singleton/@ApplicationScoped/@Dependent → @Repository, constructor injection for EntityUtils. AbstractDAO unchanged (uses @PersistenceContext which Spring supports).\n\n   - **All feature impl files** (~25 files) (Modified) - @Singleton/@Dependent → @Service, field @Inject → constructor injection\n\n   - **Model builders** (ArticleModelBuilder, UserModelBuilder, CommentBuilder, TagBuilder) (Modified) - @Singleton → @Component, constructor injection\n\n   - **EntityUtils.java** (Modified) - @ApplicationScoped → @Component, constructor injection, removed @Named qualifier\n\n   - **Request model files** (NewArticleRequest, NewCommentRequest, UpdateArticleRequest) (Modified) - Removed `jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable` import\n\n   - **smoke.py** (Created) - Comprehensive Python smoke test covering all API endpoints (tags, user registration, login, current user, update user, create/get/update/delete article, favorite/unfavorite, comments, profiles, follow/unfollow, article filtering, feed)\n\n   - **start.sh** (Modified) - Changed from `mvn clean liberty:run` to `mvn clean package -DskipTests -q` then `java -jar target/realworld-spring.jar`\n\n   - **Deleted files**: persistence.xml, beans.xml, microprofile-config.properties, server.xml (entire liberty dir), AuthenticationFilter.java, AuthorizationFilter.java, DecodedJWTSecurityContext.java, EmptySecurityContext.java, Secured.java, NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper.java, BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java, BusinessExceptionMapper.java, InfrastructureExceptionMapper.java, all old test files under src/test/\n\n4. Errors and Fixes:\n   - **mvnw not found in Docker container**: The `.dockerignore` file excluded `mvnw`, `.mvn/`, and `mvnw.cmd`. Fixed by changing start.sh to use `mvn` directly (available in the `maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble` base image) instead of `./mvnw`.\n   - **Docker port syntax error**: `ASSIGNED_PORT=$(docker port ...)` caused a bash syntax error in the tool. Worked around by running `docker port` as a separate command.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Successfully migrated the entire application from Jakarta EE (OpenLiberty) to Spring Boot 3.4.3\n   - The application starts successfully in Docker with Spring Boot embedded Tomcat\n   - PostgreSQL database connection works (HikariPool started)\n   - Hibernate schema generation (create-drop) works\n   - Still pending: smoke test execution and fixing any runtime issues\n\n6. All User Messages:\n   - Message 1: Comprehensive migration instructions with detailed checklist, environment constraints, Docker isolation requirements, migration workflow steps (dependency migration, config updates, code refactoring, build modifications, compilation/testing, documentation), validation protocol, error handling requirements, and output format specification. The migration is from Jakarta EE to Spring Boot, one-shot execution, all files within the application root directory only.\n   - Message 2: (System reminder about TodoWrite tool - no user content)\n   - Message 3: (System reminder about TodoWrite tool - no user content)\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Execute smoke tests against the running container (port 33734)\n   - Address any runtime errors or test failures\n   - Iterate: fix issues → rebuild → retest as needed\n   - Create CHANGELOG.md documenting all actions, errors, and resolutions\n   - Generate the final migration report in the specified Markdown format\n\n8. Current Work:\n   The Docker container is running successfully with Spring Boot started. The last action was confirming the application started correctly via `docker logs`:\n   ```\n   :: Spring Boot ::                (v3.4.3)\n   ...\n   Started App in 7.072 seconds (process running for 7.679)\n   ```\n   The container is running on dynamically assigned port 33734 (host) → 8080 (container). Container name: `scarf_1773466949_876546_app`.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Execute the smoke tests against the running container. The smoke test file is at `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/smoke.py` and should be run with `BASE_URL=http://localhost:33734 python3 smoke.py` or executed inside the container with `docker exec scarf_1773466949_876546_app python3 /app/smoke.py`. This is directly in line with the migration checklist: \"Build the application as a Docker image, run the container to ensure the service starts successfully, and execute any generated smoke tests against or within running container to verify the migrated application behaves as expected.\".\nPlease continue the conversation from where we left it off without asking the user any further questions. Continue with the last task that you were asked to work on."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"cf399f89-9f3b-42a