{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014U4CtS3eDpCrYxEkL7mHrC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security;\n     2→\n     3→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter.JwtAuthenticationFilter;\n     4→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\n     5→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n     6→import org.springframework.http.HttpMethod;\n     7→import org.springframework.security.config.annotation.web.builders.HttpSecurity;\n     8→import org.springframework.security.config.annotation.web.configuration.EnableWebSecurity;\n     9→import org.springframework.security.config.http.SessionCreationPolicy;\n    10→import org.springframework.security.web.SecurityFilterChain;\n    11→import org.springframework.security.web.authentication.UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter;\n    12→import org.springframework.web.cors.CorsConfiguration;\n    13→import org.springframework.web.cors.CorsConfigurationSource;\n    14→import org.springframework.web.cors.UrlBasedCorsConfigurationSource;\n    15→\n    16→import java.util.Arrays;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→\n    19→@Configuration\n    20→@EnableWebSecurity\n    21→public class SecurityConfig {\n    22→\n    23→    private final JwtAuthenticationFilter jwtAuthenticationFilter;\n    24→\n    25→    public SecurityConfig(JwtAuthenticationFilter jwtAuthenticationFilter) {\n    26→        this.jwtAuthenticationFilter = jwtAuthenticationFilter;\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    @Bean\n    30→    public SecurityFilterChain filterChain(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {\n    31→        http\n    32→            .cors(cors -> cors.configurationSource(corsConfigurationSource()))\n    33→            .csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable())\n    34→            .sessionManagement(session -> session.sessionCreationPolicy(SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS))\n    35→            .authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth\n    36→                .requestMatchers(HttpMethod.POST, \"/api/users\", \"/api/users/login\").permitAll()\n    37→                .requestMatchers(HttpMethod.GET, \"/api/articles\", \"/api/articles/*\", \"/api/articles/*/comments\", \"/api/tags\", \"/api/profiles/*\").permitAll()\n    38→                .anyRequest().authenticated()\n    39→            )\n    40→            .addFilterBefore(jwtAuthenticationFilter, UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter.class);\n    41→\n    42→        return http.build();\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    @Bean\n    46→    public CorsConfigurationSource corsConfigurationSource() {\n    47→        CorsConfiguration configuration = new CorsConfiguration();\n    48→        configuration.setAllowedOrigins(List.of(\"*\"));\n    49→        configuration.setAllowedMethods(Arrays.asList(\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\", \"OPTIONS\"));\n    50→        configuration.setAllowedHeaders(List.of(\"*\"));\n    51→        UrlBasedCorsConfigurationSource source = new UrlBasedCorsConfigurationSource();\n    52→        source.registerCorsConfiguration(\"/api/**\", configuration);\n    53→        return source;\n    54→    }\n    55→}\n    56→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"843c3feb-5847-4a1f-a87c-fb8b8a4203ed"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01K2yqg5AYCNfs7CcMLNYYQQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\n     6→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\n     7→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\n     8→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n     9→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Primary;\n    10→\n    11→@Configuration\n    12→public class SerializerConfig {\n    13→\n    14→    @Bean(name = \"wrappingObjectMapper\")\n    15→    @Primary\n    16→    public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n    17→        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    18→        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    19→        objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    20→        objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    21→        return objectMapper;\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    @Bean(name = \"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    25→    public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n    26→        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    27→    }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"f29319d3-f65e-41ab-97fd-7c013dcd85af"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Fih8UgQqeBxc2LZcygVak6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.TagsResponse;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTags;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     6→import org.springframework.http.MediaType;\n     7→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n     8→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\n     9→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\n    10→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;\n    11→\n    12→import java.util.List;\n    13→\n    14→@RestController\n    15→@RequestMapping(\"/api/tags\")\n    16→public class TagsResource {\n    17→\n    18→    private final FindTags findTags;\n    19→\n    20→    public TagsResource(FindTags findTags) {\n    21→        this.findTags = findTags;\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    @GetMapping(produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    25→    public ResponseEntity<TagsResponse> getTags() {\n    26→        List<Tag> tags = findTags.handle();\n    27→        return ResponseEntity.ok(new TagsResponse(tags));\n    28→    }\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"fe4f3fe0-4a01-47c4-b7c3-c68affb43f92"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BkRCo5H237BuU1jtpqcRrL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.Getter;\n     4→import lombok.Setter;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     6→\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     9→\n    10→@Getter\n    11→@Setter\n    12→public class TagsResponse {\n    13→\n    14→    private List<String> tags;\n    15→\n    16→    public TagsResponse(List<Tag> tags) {\n    17→        this.tags = tags.stream().map(Tag::getName).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    18→    }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"47cc8c0b-88cb-4eda-ace4-50ce0ff4883b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015wpvkTKvRJZKaqUdQWCSc2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.LoginRequestWrapper;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewUserRequestWrapper;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.UserResponse;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateUser;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.UnauthorizedException;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\n    15→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\n    16→import org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\n    17→import org.springframework.http.MediaType;\n    18→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    19→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n    20→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n    21→\n    22→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n    23→\n    24→@RestController\n    25→@RequestMapping(\"/api/users\")\n    26→public class UsersResource {\n    27→\n    28→    private final CreateUser createUser;\n    29→    private final LoginUser loginUser;\n    30→    private final TokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    31→    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    32→\n    33→    public UsersResource(\n    34→            CreateUser createUser,\n    35→            LoginUser loginUser,\n    36→            TokenProvider tokenProvider,\n    37→            @Qualifier(\"wrappingObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper) {\n    38→        this.createUser = createUser;\n    39→        this.loginUser = loginUser;\n    40→        this.tokenProvider = tokenProvider;\n    41→        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    @PostMapping(consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    45→    @Transactional\n    46→    public ResponseEntity<String> create(\n    47→            @Valid @RequestBody NewUserRequestWrapper newUserRequest) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    48→        final var user = createUser.handle(newUserRequest.getUser().toCreateUserInput());\n    49→        final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    50→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n    51→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new UserResponse(user, token)));\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    @PostMapping(value = \"/login\", consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    55→    public ResponseEntity<String> login(\n    56→            @Valid @RequestBody LoginRequestWrapper loginRequest) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    57→        User user;\n    58→        try {\n    59→            user = loginUser.handle(loginRequest.getUser().toLoginUserInput());\n    60→        } catch (UserNotFoundException | InvalidPasswordException ex) {\n    61→            throw new UnauthorizedException();\n    62→        }\n    63→        final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    64→        return ResponseEntity.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new UserResponse(user, token)));\n    65→    }\n    66→}\n    67→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"9351137a-cf66-4b1c-8468-8e9473bcf70f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019M1eJqY2wxjdiob5mfrmZw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewArticleRequestWrapper;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewCommentRequestWrapper;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.UpdateArticleRequestWrapper;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\n    12→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\n    13→import org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\n    14→import org.springframework.http.MediaType;\n    15→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    16→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n    17→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n    18→\n    19→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n    20→import java.util.List;\n    21→import java.util.UUID;\n    22→\n    23→@RestController\n    24→@RequestMapping(\"/api/articles\")\n    25→public class ArticlesResource {\n    26→\n    27→    private final FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter;\n    28→    private final CreateArticle createArticle;\n    29→    private final FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter findMostRecentArticlesByFilter;\n    30→    private final FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    31→    private final UpdateArticleBySlug updateArticleBySlug;\n    32→    private final DeleteArticleBySlug deleteArticleBySlug;\n    33→    private final CreateComment createComment;\n    34→    private final DeleteComment deleteComment;\n    35→    private final FindCommentsByArticleSlug findCommentsByArticleSlug;\n    36→    private final FavoriteArticle favoriteArticle;\n    37→    private final UnfavoriteArticle unfavoriteArticle;\n    38→    private final ResourceUtils resourceUtils;\n    39→    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    40→    private final ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper;\n    41→\n    42→    public ArticlesResource(\n    43→            FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter,\n    44→            CreateArticle createArticle,\n    45→            FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter findMostRecentArticlesByFilter,\n    46→            FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug,\n    47→            UpdateArticleBySlug updateArticleBySlug,\n    48→            DeleteArticleBySlug deleteArticleBySlug,\n    49→            CreateComment createComment,\n    50→            DeleteComment deleteComment,\n    51→            FindCommentsByArticleSlug findCommentsByArticleSlug,\n    52→            FavoriteArticle favoriteArticle,\n    53→            UnfavoriteArticle unfavoriteArticle,\n    54→            ResourceUtils resourceUtils,\n    55→            @Qualifier(\"wrappingObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper,\n    56→            @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper) {\n    57→        this.findArticlesByFilter = findArticlesByFilter;\n    58→        this.createArticle = createArticle;\n    59→        this.findMostRecentArticlesByFilter = findMostRecentArticlesByFilter;\n    60→        this.findArticleBySlug = findArticleBySlug;\n    61→        this.updateArticleBySlug = updateArticleBySlug;\n    62→        this.deleteArticleBySlug = deleteArticleBySlug;\n    63→        this.createComment = createComment;\n    64→        this.deleteComment = deleteComment;\n    65→        this.findCommentsByArticleSlug = findCommentsByArticleSlug;\n    66→        this.favoriteArticle = favoriteArticle;\n    67→        this.unfavoriteArticle = unfavoriteArticle;\n    68→        this.resourceUtils = resourceUtils;\n    69→        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n    70→        this.noWrapObjectMapper = noWrapObjectMapper;\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    @GetMapping(value = \"/feed\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    74→    public ResponseEntity<String> feed(\n    75→            @RequestParam(defaultValue = \"0\") int offset,\n    76→            @RequestParam(defaultValue = \"0\") int limit) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    77→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n    78→        final var articlesFilter =\n    79→                new ArticleFilter(offset, resourceUtils.getLimit(limit), loggedUserId, null, null, null);\n    80→        final var articlesPageResult = findMostRecentArticlesByFilter.handle(articlesFilter);\n    81→        return ResponseEntity.ok(noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n    82→                resourceUtils.articlesResponse(articlesPageResult, loggedUserId)));\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    @GetMapping(produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    86→    public ResponseEntity<String> getArticles(\n    87→            @RequestParam(defaultValue = \"0\") int offset,\n    88→            @RequestParam(defaultValue = \"0\") int limit,\n    89→            @RequestParam(required = false) List<String> tag,\n    90→            @RequestParam(required = false) List<String> author,\n    91→            @RequestParam(required = false) List<String> favorited) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    92→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n    93→        final var filter =\n    94→                new ArticleFilter(\n    95→                        offset, resourceUtils.getLimit(limit), loggedUserId, tag, author, favorited);\n    96→        final var articlesPageResult = findArticlesByFilter.handle(filter);\n    97→        return ResponseEntity.ok(noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n    98→                resourceUtils.articlesResponse(articlesPageResult, loggedUserId)));\n    99→    }\n   100→\n   101→    @PostMapping(consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n   102→    @Transactional\n   103→    public ResponseEntity<String> create(\n   104→            @Valid @RequestBody NewArticleRequestWrapper newArticleRequest) throws JsonProcessingException {\n   105→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n   106→        final var article = createArticle.handle(newArticleRequest.getArticle().toNewArticleInput(loggedUserId));\n   107→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n   108→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId)));\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    @GetMapping(value = \"/{slug}\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n   112→    public ResponseEntity<String> findBySlug(@PathVariable String slug) throws JsonProcessingException {\n   113→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n   114→        return ResponseEntity.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, null)));\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    @PutMapping(value = \"/{slug}\", consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n   118→    @Transactional\n   119→    public ResponseEntity<String> update(\n   120→            @PathVariable String slug,\n   121→            @Valid @RequestBody UpdateArticleRequestWrapper updateArticleRequest) throws JsonProcessingException {\n   122→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n   123→        final var updatedArticle =\n   124→                updateArticleBySlug.handle(updateArticleRequest.getArticle().toUpdateArticleInput(loggedUserId, slug));\n   125→        return ResponseEntity.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(resourceUtils.articleResponse(updatedArticle, null)));\n   126→    }\n   127→\n   128→    @DeleteMapping(value = \"/{slug}\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n   129→    @Transactional\n   130→    public ResponseEntity<Void> delete(@PathVariable String slug) {\n   131→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n   132→        deleteArticleBySlug.handle(loggedUserId, slug);\n   133→        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n   134→    }\n   135→\n   136→    @GetMapping(value = \"/{slug}/comments\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n   137→    public ResponseEntity<String> getCommentsBySlug(@PathVariable String slug) throws JsonProcessingException {\n   138→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n   139→        final var comments = findCommentsByArticleSlug.handle(slug);\n   140→        return ResponseEntity.ok(noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n   141→                resourceUtils.commentsResponse(comments, loggedUserId)));\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    @PostMapping(value = \"/{slug}/comments\", consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n   145→    @Transactional\n   146→    public ResponseEntity<String> createComment(\n   147→            @PathVariable String slug,\n   148→            @Valid @RequestBody NewCommentRequestWrapper newCommentRequest) throws JsonProcessingException {\n   149→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n   150→        final var comment =\n   151→                createComment.handle(newCommentRequest.getComment().toNewCommentInput(loggedUserId, slug));\n   152→        return ResponseEntity.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n   153→                resourceUtils.commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId)));\n   154→    }\n   155→\n   156→    @DeleteMapping(value = \"/{slug}/comments/{id}\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n   157→    @Transactional\n   158→    public ResponseEntity<Void> deleteComment(\n   159→            @PathVariable String slug,\n   160→            @PathVariable UUID id) {\n   161→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n   162→        deleteComment.handle(new DeleteCommentInput(id, loggedUserId, slug));\n   163→        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    @PostMapping(value = \"/{slug}/favorite\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n   167→    @Transactional\n   168→    public ResponseEntity<String> favoriteArticle(@PathVariable String slug) throws JsonProcessingException {\n   169→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n   170→        favoriteArticle.handle(slug, loggedUserId);\n   171→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n   172→        return ResponseEntity.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n   173→                resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId)));\n   174→    }\n   175→\n   176→    @DeleteMapping(value = \"/{slug}/favorite\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n   177→    @Transactional\n   178→    public ResponseEntity<String> unfavoriteArticle(@PathVariable String slug) throws JsonProcessingException {\n   179→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n   180→        unfavoriteArticle.handle(slug, loggedUserId);\n   181→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n   182→        return ResponseEntity.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n   183→                resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId)));\n   184→    }\n   185→}\n   186→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"3ebc29b1-6bad-402d-9e68-a21c75eeb75d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012EEs6XZgBkXEWrphfEwZZX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FollowUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfollowUserByUsername;\n     8→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\n     9→import org.springframework.http.MediaType;\n    10→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    11→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n    12→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n    13→\n    14→@RestController\n    15→@RequestMapping(\"/api/profiles\")\n    16→public class ProfilesResource {\n    17→\n    18→    private final FollowUserByUsername followUserByUsername;\n    19→    private final UnfollowUserByUsername unfollowUserByUsername;\n    20→    private final ResourceUtils resourceUtils;\n    21→    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    22→\n    23→    public ProfilesResource(\n    24→            FollowUserByUsername followUserByUsername,\n    25→            UnfollowUserByUsername unfollowUserByUsername,\n    26→            ResourceUtils resourceUtils,\n    27→            @Qualifier(\"wrappingObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper) {\n    28→        this.followUserByUsername = followUserByUsername;\n    29→        this.unfollowUserByUsername = unfollowUserByUsername;\n    30→        this.resourceUtils = resourceUtils;\n    31→        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    @GetMapping(value = \"/{username}\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    35→    public ResponseEntity<String> getProfile(@PathVariable String username) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    36→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n    37→        final var profileResponse = resourceUtils.profileResponse(username, loggedUserId);\n    38→        return ResponseEntity.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(profileResponse));\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    @PostMapping(value = \"/{username}/follow\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    42→    @Transactional\n    43→    public ResponseEntity<String> follow(@PathVariable String username) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    44→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n    45→        followUserByUsername.handle(loggedUserId, username);\n    46→        return ResponseEntity.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n    47→                resourceUtils.profileResponse(username, loggedUserId)));\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    @DeleteMapping(value = \"/{username}/follow\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    51→    @Transactional\n    52→    public ResponseEntity<String> unfollow(@PathVariable String username) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    53→        final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId();\n    54→        unfollowUserByUsername.handle(loggedUserId, username);\n    55→        return ResponseEntity.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n    56→                resourceUtils.profileResponse(username, loggedUserId)));\n    57→    }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"86ea9193-7a20-4465-8814-1bc3890f2b3b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SHaeDSjBBxyjKHonq1365a","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolationException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.ForbiddenException;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.UnauthorizedException;\n    10→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\n    11→import org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\n    12→import org.springframework.http.MediaType;\n    13→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    14→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.ExceptionHandler;\n    15→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestControllerAdvice;\n    16→\n    17→@RestControllerAdvice\n    18→public class GlobalExceptionHandler {\n    19→\n    20→    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    21→\n    22→    public GlobalExceptionHandler(@Qualifier(\"wrappingObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper) {\n    23→        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    @ExceptionHandler(UserNotFoundException.class)\n    27→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleUserNotFound(UserNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    28→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n    29→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    30→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    @ExceptionHandler(ArticleNotFoundException.class)\n    34→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleArticleNotFound(ArticleNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    35→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n    36→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    37→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @ExceptionHandler(TagNotFoundException.class)\n    41→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleTagNotFound(TagNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    42→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n    43→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    44→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    @ExceptionHandler(CommentNotFoundException.class)\n    48→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleCommentNotFound(CommentNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    49→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n    50→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    51→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    @ExceptionHandler({EmailAlreadyExistsException.class, UsernameAlreadyExistsException.class})\n    55→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleConflict(BusinessException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    56→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CONFLICT)\n    57→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    58→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    @ExceptionHandler(InvalidPasswordException.class)\n    62→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleInvalidPassword(InvalidPasswordException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    63→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED)\n    64→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    65→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    @ExceptionHandler(ModelValidationException.class)\n    69→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleModelValidation(ModelValidationException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    70→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n    71→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    72→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    @ExceptionHandler(UnauthorizedException.class)\n    76→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleUnauthorized(UnauthorizedException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    77→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED)\n    78→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    79→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(\"Unauthorized\")));\n    80→    }\n    81→\n    82→    @ExceptionHandler(ForbiddenException.class)\n    83→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleForbidden(ForbiddenException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    84→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN)\n    85→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    86→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(\"Forbidden\")));\n    87→    }\n    88→\n    89→    @ExceptionHandler(ConstraintViolationException.class)\n    90→    public ResponseEntity<String> handleConstraintViolation(ConstraintViolationException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    91→        ErrorResponse errorResponse = new ErrorResponse();\n    92→        ex.getConstraintViolations().forEach(violation -> errorResponse.getBody().add(violation.getMessage()));\n    93→        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n    94→                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    95→                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse));\n    96→    }\n    97→}\n    98→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"53918304-e29e-4bc9-8380-882122964f68"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BL6HqDvm8q3wT2xffbTL8F","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter;\n     2→\n     3→import com.auth0.jwt.exceptions.JWTVerificationException;\n     4→import com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\n     5→import jakarta.servlet.FilterChain;\n     6→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n     7→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n     8→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n    11→import org.springframework.security.authentication.UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken;\n    12→import org.springframework.security.core.authority.SimpleGrantedAuthority;\n    13→import org.springframework.security.core.context.SecurityContextHolder;\n    14→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    15→import org.springframework.web.filter.OncePerRequestFilter;\n    16→\n    17→import java.io.IOException;\n    18→import java.util.Arrays;\n    19→import java.util.List;\n    20→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    21→\n    22→@Component\n    23→public class JwtAuthenticationFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {\n    24→\n    25→    private static final String AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX = \"Token \";\n    26→\n    27→    private final TokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    28→\n    29→    public JwtAuthenticationFilter(TokenProvider tokenProvider) {\n    30→        this.tokenProvider = tokenProvider;\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    @Override\n    34→    protected void doFilterInternal(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response,\n    35→                                     FilterChain filterChain) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    36→        String authorizationHeader = request.getHeader(\"Authorization\");\n    37→\n    38→        if (authorizationHeader != null && authorizationHeader.startsWith(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX)) {\n    39→            String token = authorizationHeader.substring(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX.length());\n    40→            try {\n    41→                DecodedJWT decodedJWT = tokenProvider.verify(token);\n    42→                String userId = decodedJWT.getSubject();\n    43→                Role[] roles = tokenProvider.extractRoles(decodedJWT);\n    44→\n    45→                List<SimpleGrantedAuthority> authorities = Arrays.stream(roles)\n    46→                        .map(role -> new SimpleGrantedAuthority(\"ROLE_\" + role.name()))\n    47→                        .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    48→\n    49→                UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken authentication =\n    50→                        new UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken(userId, null, authorities);\n    51→                SecurityContextHolder.getContext().setAuthentication(authentication);\n    52→            } catch (JWTVerificationException ex) {\n    53→                // Invalid token - continue without authentication\n    54→            }\n    55→        }\n    56→\n    57→        filterChain.doFilter(request, response);\n    58→    }\n    59→}\n    60→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"fd58f876-e9b5-4c82-80ca-4d0a701f707d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDcQMry2wcEfAzGDDW8qfK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have successfully retrieved the contents of all nine files you requested. Here's a brief summary of each file:\n\n1. SecurityConfig.java:\n   - Spring Security configuration for the application\n   - Configures CORS, CSRF, session management\n   - Sets up authentication rules for different endpoints\n   - Allows public access to user registration, login, and read-only article/profile endpoints\n\n2. SerializerConfig.java:\n   - Jackson ObjectMapper configuration\n   - Creates two ObjectMapper beans:\n     a. `wrappingObjectMapper`: Enables root value wrapping/unwrapping\n     b. `noWrapRootValueObjectMapper`: Standard ObjectMapper with JavaTimeModule\n\n3. TagsResource.java:\n   - REST controller for tags endpoint (/api/tags)\n   - Provides a GET method to retrieve all tags\n   - Uses `FindTags` domain feature to fetch tags\n   - Returns tags as a `TagsResponse`\n\n4. TagsResponse.java:\n   - Response model for tags\n   - Converts `List<Tag>` to `List<String>` of tag names\n   - Uses Lombok annotations for getters/setters\n\n5. UsersResource.java:\n   - REST controller for user-related operations (/api/users)\n   - Handles user registration and login\n   - Uses JWT token generation\n   - Supports creating new users and user authentication\n\n6. ArticlesResource.java:\n   - Comprehensive REST controller for article-related operations (/api/articles)\n   - Supports CRUD operations on articles\n   - Handles article feed, filtering, comments, and favorites\n   - Uses various domain features for article management\n\n7. ProfilesResource.java:\n   - REST controller for user profiles (/api/profiles)\n   - Provides endpoints for getting profiles\n   - Supports following and unfollowing users\n\n8. GlobalExceptionHandler.java:\n   - Centralized exception handling for the application\n   - Handles various exceptions like:\n     - Not found exceptions (User, Article, Tag, Comment)\n     - Conflict exceptions\n     - Validation exceptions\n     - Authorization exceptions\n\n9. JwtAuthenticationFilter.java:\n   - Custom JWT authentication filter\n   - Intercepts requests and validates JWT tokens\n   - Extracts user ID and roles from tokens\n   - Sets up Spring Security authentication context\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspects of these files or provide any additional analysis?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"f49df2de-e39a-46df-9aa8-85a32969cb13"}
