{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01G4PQNYY2Zn3WXrmwmwaeLn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The logs confirm it: `Root name ('user') does not match expected ('NewUserRequestWrapper')`. The wrapping ObjectMapper as `@Primary` causes Spring MVC's message converter to use `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE`, which tries to unwrap `{\"user\":...}` and expects the root name to be `NewUserRequestWrapper` (class name) since there's no `@JsonRootName` annotation on the wrapper.\n\nThe fix strategy:\n1. **Make the non-wrapping ObjectMapper `@Primary`** so Spring MVC uses it by default for HTTP message conversion\n2. **Remove `@Primary` from the wrapping ObjectMapper** — it's only used explicitly in controllers via `@Qualifier`\n3. **Fix TagsResource** to use manual serialization or the non-wrapping ObjectMapper since it returns `TagsResponse` directly without `@JsonRootName`\n\nLet me implement all the fixes:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2017,"cache_read_input_tokens":50273,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2017,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":670},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"98c8e06b-9087-4285-9496-8eb17d3b8ade"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01G4PQNYY2Zn3WXrmwmwaeLn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01NfwifKPB4tWrCEEYctsG7B","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/config/SerializerConfig.java","old_string":"    @Bean(name = \"wrappingObjectMapper\")\n    @Primary\n    public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n        return objectMapper;\n    }\n\n    @Bean(name = \"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    }","new_string":"    @Bean(name = \"wrappingObjectMapper\")\n    public ObjectMapper wrappingObjectMapper() {\n        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n        return objectMapper;\n    }\n\n    @Bean(name = \"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    @Primary\n    public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    }"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2017,"cache_read_input_tokens":50273,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2017,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":670},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b