{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012xopdKfafGyQUUjhicVSiN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Still 403. The request reaches Spring Security, gets denied. Since `GET /api/articles` works but `POST /api/users` doesn't even though both are in `permitAll()`, the issue must be with how Spring Security is matching POST requests.\n\nWait — I think I see the issue. In Spring Boot 3 with `requestMatchers()`, the path pattern `/api/users` might only match the exact path. But the POST mapping on `UsersResource` is at `@PostMapping` on the class `@RequestMapping(\"/api/users\")`. The path should be exactly `/api/users`.\n\nActually, let me re-read the SecurityConfig more carefully. The issue might be that the Spring Security filter chain has some other issue. Let me add debug logging:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":574,"cache_read_input_tokens":57099,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":574,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":275},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"7c382474-e754-4405-898c-caefa2545602"}
