{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GVC56mnj7AwSsmRDyLKts3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→server.port=8080\n     2→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/postgres_db\n     3→spring.datasource.username=postgres_user\n     4→spring.datasource.password=S3cret\n     5→spring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.postgresql.Driver\n     6→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n     7→spring.jpa.show-sql=false\n     8→spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect\n     9→spring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n    10→jwt.issuer=users-service\n    11→jwt.secret=secret123\n    12→jwt.expiration.time.minutes=10\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"831cbcfc-29f6-4146-bc42-a8e1b42264b4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SbuZN5YPqa1qUSDKjnbwtF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me think about this differently. The `requestMatchers(HttpMethod.POST, \"/api/users\", \"/api/users/login\").permitAll()` should work. But maybe the issue is that Spring Boot 3 defaults to **path pattern matching** with `PathPatternParser` for servlet security, and there could be a conflict with how the request matchers are set up.\n\nActually, I just realized something: Spring Boot 3 Spring Security might be applying a **request cache** and the 403 could be coming from something else entirely. Let me check if the `JwtAuthenticationFilter` might be interfering — it runs before the authentication filter. If the filter somehow causes an error or sets a denied authentication on non-authenticated requests...\n\nLooking at the JwtAuthenticationFilter code — it only sets authentication if a token is provided. If no token, it just continues the chain. That should be fine.\n\nWait — I bet the problem is that the wrapping ObjectMapper, being the primary one, is used by Spring's `MappingJackson2HttpMessageConverter`. When Spring tries to parse the POST body with `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled, it fails with `HttpMessageNotReadableException`. Spring Security then wraps this as a 403 because the error handling fires within the security filter chain.\n\nActually no — the first smoke test worked (tags endpoint), and the 403 happens before body parsing for POST requests. But wait, the logs show `HttpMessageNotReadableException` for one of the POST requests. So for some requests it gets past security but fails on parsing, while for others it gets blocked at 403.\n\nActually, I need to look at this more carefully. The 403 might be because of Spring Security's `AuthorizationFilter` returning 403 for POST requests. Let me check if there is a problem with the `permitAll()` rule for POST. \n\nLet me try a completely different approach — make the security config more permissive to test:\n\nActually, the simplest fix is to check if CSRF is really disabled. Sometimes in Spring Boot 3, the lambda-style CSRF disable doesn't work if the security filter chain configuration order is wrong. Let me also check if there is perhaps a second SecurityFilterChain bean or another configuration conflicting.\n\nLet me look at this from a different angle. Let me check if there's a Spring Security auto-configuration causing an additional filter chain:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":960,"cache_read_input_tokens":57673,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":960,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":685},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8d75e0c-f395-45d5-b7d7-3f60b39c8ca5","uuid":"34250434-cf55-4136-b287-ae19d7c22cc9"}
